==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin (''prosequor'': '''to follow''': '''to persue''')
===Transitive verb===
to prosecute.
#{{law}} To persue a criminal charge against another. e.g. The state will '''prosecute''' the murderer.
#{{law}} To procede with an action or process. e.g. I intend to '''prosecute''' my appeal.
# To follow with the intent of acomplishing an end. e.g. He '''prosecuted''' his scheme, and became a millionaire.
===Intransitive verb===
#{{obsolete}} To follow after.